    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU2 VAD hemolysis prediction is accepted for submission purposes. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been evaluated: 7 factors assessed (all with achieved levels below required levels for MRL 5) and 6 factors not assessed (flagged as epistemic gaps). Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed on primary operating inputs. Note: the ContextOfUse does not specify applicability constraints or an operating envelope, leaving the model's valid range of use unspecified. This constitutes an unresolved ontological gap (W-ON-02) that was not identified during the assessment cycle.",
